label: Newton Plantation Money Renters Book 1862
description: This book contains records of the rents paid by Money Renters on Newton Plantation for the year 1862.  It includes information on  the rents  for the period, the quantity of land rented, the names of the tenants, the weekly rent paid, the amount due for that period, the amount  paid and any outstanding arrears. This book, along with a  second book, a list of the wages and rents for stock keepers and watchmen for the year 1862, are both contained in one physical book.  The physical book is arranged in such a way that each section begins with a front cover.
